      "message": "It doesn\u0027t exactly do what we want. See for example the unittest:\n\n```\nTEST(ParameterList, toString) {\n    ParameterList list;\n    list.add2(\"foo\", \"bar\");\n    list.add(\" zoo \");\n    EXPECT_EQ(3U, list.size());\n#ifdef _WIN32\n    const char* expect_str \u003d  \"foo bar \\\" zoo \\\"\";\n#else\n    const char* expect_str \u003d \"foo bar \u0027 zoo \u0027\";\n#endif\n    EXPECT_STREQ(expect_str, list.toString().c_str());\n}\n```\n\n(toString calls quoteCommandLine for each parameter)\n\n- You would get different behavior on windows/posix.\n- Not every command gets quoted\n- No escaping of special characters on posix",
